sburg. From the end of 1914 to the middle of 1919 I read exactly one thousand and eighteen books … kept count of them. On my way to Germany I was stranded for three months in Moscow and got married there. Since 1920, I had been living in Berlin. On the ninth of May 1930, having passed the age of thirty-five …

